#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:4
msgid "funced - edit a function interactively"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:7
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:9
msgid "funced [OPTIONS] NAME"
msgstr "funced [OPTIONS] NAME"

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:14
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:16
msgid ""
"``funced`` provides an interface to edit the definition of the function "
"*NAME*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:18
msgid ""
"If the ``$VISUAL`` environment variable is set, it will be used as the "
"program to edit the function. If ``$VISUAL`` is unset but ``$EDITOR`` is "
"set, that will be used. Otherwise, a built-in editor will be used. Note that "
"to enter a literal newline using the built-in editor you should press :kbd:"
"`Alt`\\ +\\ :kbd:`Enter`. Pressing :kbd:`Enter` signals that you are done "
"editing the function. This does not apply to an external editor like emacs "
"or vim."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:20
msgid ""
"``funced`` will try to edit the original file that a function is defined in, "
"which might include variable definitions or helper functions as well. If "
"changes cannot be saved to the original file, a copy will be created in the "
"user's function directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:22
msgid ""
"If there is no function called *NAME*, a new function will be created with "
"the specified name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:24
msgid "**-e command** or **--editor command**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:25
msgid ""
"Open the function body inside the text editor given by the command (for "
"example, **-e vi**). The special command ``fish`` will use the built-in "
"editor (same as specifying **-i**)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:27
msgid "**-i** or **--interactive**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:28
msgid ""
"Force opening the function body in the built-in editor even if ``$VISUAL`` "
"or ``$EDITOR`` is defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:30
msgid "**-s** or **--save**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:31
msgid "Automatically save the function after successfully editing it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:33
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:34
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:37
msgid "Example"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:39
msgid "Say you want to modify your prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:41
msgid "Run::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:43
msgid ">_ funced fish_prompt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:45
msgid ""
"This will open up your editor, allowing you to modify the function. When "
"you're done, save and quit. Fish will reload the function, so you should see "
"the changes right away."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:47
msgid "When you're done, use::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:49
msgid ">_ funcsave fish_prompt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/funced.rst:51
msgid "For more, see :doc:`funcsave <funcsave>`."
msgstr ""
